        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 2 at 4:56PM EDT by NWS Raleigh NC</headline>
        <description>At 456 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Alton, or near Turbeville, moving east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts in excess of 30 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Roxboro, Concord, Bethel Hill, Mayo Reservoir, and Hyco Lake.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
